cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC

The paper discusses the feasibility of using a hybrid of unicast and broadcast in cellular networks for high-traffic services, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also considers cost effectiveness, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and system optimization (cs.SI). Additionally, the proposed periodic broadcasting service involves cooperation between mobile network operators and content providers, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
